<item>
            <title>[LU-15436] seq.ctl-*.fldb parameter file stops at 4KB of output</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15436</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lctl get_param seq.ctl-&amp;#42;.fldb&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; file stops printing lines after about 4KB is printed (OST0051 if there are two MDTs). &#160;This appears to be a problem in the debugfs/seq_file handling in the kernel module, since&#160;&lt;tt&gt;lctl&lt;/tt&gt;&#160;gets a short read on its 64KB buffer and retries the read again before stopping.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;



&lt;p&gt;it may be that this is using seq_file instead of debugfs and is limited to 4KB of output?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="67918">LU-15436</key>
