                            <comment id="322365" author="adilger" created="Tue, 11 Jan 2022 18:21:52 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I hit this at OST 0x51, so 81 OSTs and 2 MDTs. I was able to simulate a large number of OSTs (432) on a smaller test system by having the &quot;start&quot; function also unmount the OST and delete the OST loopback file, to avoid filling /tmp or RAM. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="322309" author="simmonsja" created="Tue, 11 Jan 2022 14:39:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This sounds like a *pos issue. How large a system do you need to setup to duplicate this problem?&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
